@@ -0,0 +1,91 @@
+[package]
+name = "clap-noun-verb"
+version = "3.0.0"
+edition = "2021"
+rust-version = "1.70"
+license = "MIT OR Apache-2.0"
+authors = ["Sean Chatman <seanchatmangpt@gmail.com>"]
+repository = "https://github.com/seanchatmangpt/clap-noun-verb"
+documentation = "https://docs.rs/clap-noun-verb"
+homepage = "https://github.com/seanchatmangpt/clap-noun-verb"
+description = "A high-level, ergonomic API for building noun-verb CLI patterns on top of clap"
+keywords = ["cli", "clap", "noun-verb", "command-line", "typer"]
+categories = ["command-line-utilities", "development-tools"]
+readme = "README.md"
+
+[lib]
+name = "clap_noun_verb"
+path = "src/lib.rs"
+
+[dependencies]
+clap = { version = "4.5", features = ["derive"] }
+thiserror = "1.0"
+serde = { version = "1.0", features = ["derive"] }
+serde_json = "1.0"
+linkme = "0.3"
+clap-noun-verb-macros = { path = "clap-noun-verb-macros", version = "3.0.0" }
+
+[dev-dependencies]
+tokio = { version = "1.0", features = ["full"] }
+anyhow = "1.0"
+cargo-make = "0.37"
+
+[workspace.metadata.make]
+# Cargo-make configuration
+verbose = false
+
+[[example]]
+name = "basic"
+path = "examples/basic.rs"
+
+[[example]]
+name = "services"
+path = "examples/services.rs"
+
+[[example]]
+name = "collector"
+path = "examples/collector.rs"
+
+[[example]]
+name = "arguments"
+path = "examples/arguments.rs"
+
+[[example]]
+name = "framework"
+path = "examples/framework.rs"
+
+[[example]]
+name = "nested"
+path = "examples/nested.rs"
+
+[[example]]
+name = "attribute_macro"
+path = "examples/attribute_macro.rs"
+
+[[example]]
+name = "validation"
+path = "examples/validation.rs"
+
+[lints.rust]
+# Core team best practices - deny unsafe patterns
+unsafe_code = "deny"
+bare_trait_objects = "warn"
+
+[lints.clippy]
+# Error handling - never use unwrap or expect in production
+unwrap_used = "deny"
+expect_used = "deny"
+panic = "deny"
+unimplemented = "deny"
+todo = "deny"
+exit = "deny"
+
+# Code quality (all at lower priority to allow specific overrides)
+all = { level = "warn", priority = -1 }
+
+# Best practices
+redundant_pattern_matching = "warn"
+unnecessary_wraps = "warn"
+too_many_arguments = "warn"
+too_many_lines = "warn"
+cognitive_complexity = "warn"

[package]
name = "clap-noun-verb"
version = "3.0.0"
edition = "2021"
rust-version = "1.70"
license = "MIT OR Apache-2.0"
authors = ["Sean Chatman <seanchatmangpt@gmail.com>"]
repository = "https://github.com/seanchatmangpt/clap-noun-verb"
documentation = "https://docs.rs/clap-noun-verb"
homepage = "https://github.com/seanchatmangpt/clap-noun-verb"
description = "A high-level, ergonomic API for building noun-verb CLI patterns on top of clap"
keywords = ["cli", "clap", "noun-verb", "command-line", "typer"]
categories = ["command-line-utilities", "development-tools"]
readme = "README.md"

[lib]
name = "clap_noun_verb"
path = "src/lib.rs"

[dependencies]
clap = { version = "4.5", features = ["derive"] }
thiserror = "1.0"
serde = { version = "1.0", features = ["derive"] }
serde_json = "1.0"
linkme = "0.3"
clap-noun-verb-macros = { path = "clap-noun-verb-macros", version = "3.0.0" }

[dev-dependencies]
tokio = { version = "1.0", features = ["full"] }
anyhow = "1.0"

[[example]]
name = "basic"
path = "examples/basic.rs"

[[example]]
name = "services"
path = "examples/services.rs"

[[example]]
name = "collector"
path = "examples/collector.rs"

[[example]]
name = "arguments"
path = "examples/arguments.rs"

[[example]]
name = "framework"
path = "examples/framework.rs"

[[example]]
name = "nested"
path = "examples/nested.rs"

[[example]]
name = "attribute_macro"
path = "examples/attribute_macro.rs"

[[example]]
name = "validation"
path = "examples/validation.rs"

[lints.rust]
# Core team best practices - deny unsafe patterns
unsafe_code = "deny"
bare_trait_objects = "warn"

[lints.clippy]
# Error handling - never use unwrap or expect in production
unwrap_used = "deny"
expect_used = "deny"
panic = "deny"
unimplemented = "deny"
todo = "deny"
exit = "deny"

# Code quality (all at lower priority to allow specific overrides)
all = { level = "warn", priority = -1 }

# Best practices
redundant_pattern_matching = "warn"
unnecessary_wraps = "warn"
too_many_arguments = "warn"
too_many_lines = "warn"
cognitive_complexity = "warn"
